data.content:
Here's what breaks in each snippet when targeting .NET 10:

---

### 1. `Form1.cs` — `ContextMenu` / `MenuItem` removed

These types were obsoleted-as-errors (WFDEV001/WFDEV002) and are **removed in .NET 10**. Replace with the `Strip` equivalents:

```csharp
var menu = new ContextMenuStrip();
menu.Items.Add(new ToolStripMenuItem("Open", null, OnOpen));
```

The event handler signature changes from `EventHandler` to accepting a `ToolStripMenuItem` sender.

---

### 2. `ImageProcessor.cs` — Wrong exception type

In .NET 10, `System.Drawing` no longer throws the misleading `OutOfMemoryException` for invalid/corrupt image files. It now throws a more appropriate exception (e.g., `ArgumentException`). Your `catch (OutOfMemoryException)` **will silently miss corrupt-file errors**:

```csharp
try
{
    using var bmp = new Bitmap(path);
    bmp.SetResolution(300, 300);
}
catch (ArgumentException ex)   // .NET 10: replaces OutOfMemoryException for bad images
{
    logger.LogError(ex, "Invalid image format");
}
catch (OutOfMemoryException ex) // keep for genuine OOM
{
    logger.LogError(ex, "Out of memory loading image");
}
```

---

### 3. `MainWindow.xaml` — Stricter `DynamicResource` behavior

In .NET 10 WPF, referencing a **missing resource key** now produces runtime trace warnings and may surface as binding failures more visibly. `MissingKey` will need to be defined in a `ResourceDictionary` or replaced with a `FallbackValue`:

```xml
<TextBlock Text="{DynamicResource MissingKey, FallbackValue='(none)'}" />
```

The empty `<Grid.ColumnDefinitions/>` and `<Grid.RowDefinitions/>` are harmless but dead code — remove them.

---

### Additional items you mentioned

| Feature | .NET 10 change | Action |
|---|---|---|
| **StatusStrip** (default rendering) | Default `RenderMode` behavior changed; visual-style rendering is now the default | Set `RenderMode = ToolStripRenderMode.Professional` explicitly if you need the old look |
| **TreeView checkboxes** | Native checkbox rendering changed; `StateImageList` is no longer used when `CheckBoxes = true` | Test checkbox appearance; remove any custom `StateImageList` workarounds that conflict with the new behavior |
